variant_descriptions.KANDW: Bitwise AND 16 bits masks k2 and k3 and place result in k1.
variant_descriptions.KANDB: Bitwise AND 8 bits masks k2 and k3 and place result in k1.
variant_descriptions.KANDQ: Bitwise AND 64 bits masks k2 and k3 and place result in k1.
variant_descriptions.KANDD: Bitwise AND 32 bits masks k2 and k3 and place result in k1.

op.text: Performs a bitwise AND between the vector mask k2 and the vector mask k3, and writes the result into vector mask k1.
